                <h2>Nutritional Needs for Horses</h2>
                <p>Horses require a balanced diet to maintain health and performance:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Forage:</strong> High-quality hay and pasture provide essential fiber and nutrients.</li>
                    <li><strong>Concentrates:</strong> Grains and concentrates can supplement energy, especially for working horses.</li>
                    <li><strong>Minerals and Vitamins:</strong> Supplements may be necessary to ensure balanced nutrition, depending on the horse's needs.</li>
                    <li><strong>Water:</strong> Fresh, clean water should be available at all times.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Consult with a veterinarian or equine nutritionist for specific dietary recommendations based on the horseâ€™s age, activity level, and health status.</p>
